  <description><![CDATA[<p>This five-star hotel is beautifully furnished in an attractive alpine style and has charming gardens with bush–covered verandas, lounging areas, and a traditional Swiss cart on display.</p>
<h2>Perfect central location</h2>
<p>You'll be just a short walk from the mountain railway and the village centre - just outside the hotel, the main train station is close by. Despite this fantastic location, you'll walk in an feel like you're on a peaceful Alpine escape, thanks to the pretty gardens and rustic décor with touches of luxury.</p>
<h2>Character, elegance, luxury, and tradition</h2>
<p>The connected lounge, bar, and restaurant are elaborately furnished with quirky traditional features and the pianist who plays during afternoon tea and in the evenings is always a delight. The spa is excellent, with an indoor pool with a current, sun terrace, steam bath, glacier grotto, Kneipp, private whirlpool, relaxation showers and two saunas.</p>
<p>On half board arrangement, you'll enjoy a generous buffet breakfast and lavish four-course evening meal. All served up by the Michelin Guide-featured kitchen.</p>]]></description>
